body_text.text:
From model for AT measured at lag 3 days, we found a reversed J-shape relationship between AT and mortality. For AT below 20.8 °C, decreasing daily mean AT was associated with increasing mortality from all causes, indicating that the cold threshold was at 20.8 °C when the log relative risk was 0 (Fig. 1
). From the model for AT measured at lag 0–1 days, a U-shape relationship was observed with the threshold of AT for heat effects estimated at 28.2 °C, above which increasing mortality was found (Fig. 2
).
